Macao Governor to Leave for Lisbon , Rome
MACAO , November 30 ( Xinhua ) -- Macao Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira will leave Macao on December 5 to attend a Portuguese state affairs conference at which the Macao issue will be discussed .
According to sources with the Governor Office , the governor will also meet with some Portuguese government officials in Lisbon and then head for Rome .
On December 19 , he will meet with the Pope at the Vatican .
Catholicism was introduced into Macao in the 16th century .
The governor will return to Macao on December 19 .
Vitor Rodrigues Pessoa , secretary for economic cooperation of the Macao government , will serve as acting governor while the governor is away .
